

Type Notes:

Binary, Octal, and Hex:

int testBinary = 0b01101101;

int testOctal = 07757;

int testHex = 0xff;


------------------------------------

Chars and String:

char charNum = 35;
char charChar = 'g';
char charArray[250] = "Test String";

Declare strings to be empty, to prevent junk data from being in the strings:

char empty_string[1000] = {};

Float:

Always use Double and not Float.

Float loses precision easily as numbers get even slightly big.


Boolean:

_Bool testTrue = 4;
_Bool testFalse = 0;

_Bool will evaluate 0 to False, and all other Ints to True.
